Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 26742cff80aa1bc278e487623e00281f9c25cd3e&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="305796" author="sebastien" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:35:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to address this requirement, we could add the ability to create id maps of a new type &lt;tt&gt;projid&lt;/tt&gt;, in addition to the already existing &lt;tt&gt;uid&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;gid&lt;/tt&gt; types. That would also require adding a new value to &lt;tt&gt;map_mode&lt;/tt&gt;. Currently it only groks &lt;tt&gt;uid_only&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;gid_only&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;both&lt;/tt&gt;, but we could add a &lt;tt&gt;projid_only&lt;/tt&gt; value. Finally, a new property named &lt;tt&gt;squash_projid&lt;/tt&gt; could be used to map all project ID to a default one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The common case of one projid allowed per nodemap would consist in having a map that just has the projid mapped to itself, the &lt;tt&gt;map_mode&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;projid_only&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;deny_unknown&lt;/tt&gt; set to 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
